title: >>> DOVER DOMINATION
body_text:
Dover: Prepare to be Taken Over!
A sport running for well over 1 year will be tested ... finally.
On February 3, 2007, on the one year anniversary of Diana's Dodgeball Dinner, Toms River High School East will host an all-painball double elimination tournament. At last, the warriors of Wall High School are challenged like never before.
A team has been formed, with the appreciated financial assistance from Ahern Printing. The 10-men army looks like this: Ryan McCrorey, Mike "Sputz", Chris Adams, Tom Adams, Kevin Adams, Chris Burke, Kevin Fitzpatrick, Justin Pierce, John Tronolone, and Kevin Megill.
Ten of the biggest names to ever compete have a golden opportunity to prove they are the most dominant dodgeball players around. Come Saturday, February 3, they will get that chance.
Further information will be released in the coming week regarding this soon-to-be classic night of dodgeball action.
**
Please Note
: DODGEBALL 75 will be moved back one week from February 3 to Saturday, February 10.
**
No Registration Needed!
It's a brand new feature right here on
dodgeball.livejournal.com
!
Who's bulletball shots hurt / sting the most?
Kevin Fitzpatrick
Chris Adams
Kevin Megill
John Tronolone
Tom Adams
John Watters

DODGEBALL 73
Ohhhhhhh yeahhhhhhhhh! It's that time again to prepare for the next big encounter, heading your way Saturday, January 20, 2007. Last year, DODGEBALL 23 was met with warm, Spring-like weather as players and spectators alike wore T-shirts for the first time in ages. What will happen this coming Saturday when DODGEBALL 73 hits Wall High School? Be there live to find out.
